---
import Base from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="About"><Fragment slot="header"><Header /></Fragment>

  <section class="pt-28 pb-16" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#f8faff 0%,#ffffff 50%,#f5f3ff 100%)">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl"><p class="sl">About</p><h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-5">Infrastructure for the genome</h1><p class="text-lg text-gray-500 max-w-xl">Protomon Labs builds the platforms, standards, and tools that make genomic research possible at scale.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 items-start">
        <div class="md:col-span-1"><div class="aspect-[3/4] rounded-xl bg-gray-50 flex items-center justify-center border border-gray-100"><img src="/logo.svg" alt="" class="w-28 h-28 opacity-30" /></div></div>
        <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>Genomic research today faces a critical infrastructure gap. Data generation outpaces our capacity to process, standardize, and share it. Variant interpretation requires coordinated pipelines, reference resources, and benchmarking frameworks that don't exist as off-the-shelf solutions. We build them.</p>
          <p>Protomon Labs develops the computational infrastructure that powers genomic discovery at scale. Our work spans variant annotation platforms, population-scale data resources, statistical method frameworks, and open benchmarking infrastructure — all designed for reproducibility, portability, and community reuse.</p>
          <p>Everything we build is open source. The foundational layer of genomics should be a shared resource — maintained collaboratively, available freely, and built to last.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50 border-y border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-xl mb-10"><p class="sl">Infrastructure</p><h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-gray-900">What we build</h2></div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        {[{t:"Variant Annotation Platforms",i:["Unified pipelines for WGS and WES","Multi-omics data integration","Cloud-native analysis infrastructure","Real-time variant prioritization","Benchmarking and validation toolchains"]},{t:"Population Genomics Infrastructure",i:["Cross-population frequency databases","Ancestry-aware analysis frameworks","Rare variant burden testing platforms","Demographic inference tooling","Admixture mapping infrastructure"]},{t:"Open Data Resources",i:["Standardized variant catalogues","Reference panels for diverse populations","Annotation knowledge bases","Community benchmarking datasets","Reproducible analysis recipes"]},{t:"Statistical Method Frameworks",i:["Portable eQTL mapping infrastructure","Fine-mapping pipelines for complex traits","PRS evaluation and benchmarking tools","Mendelian randomization frameworks","High-dimensional omics integration"]}].map((a)=>(<div class="card"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">{a.t}</h3><ul class="space-y-1.5">{a.i.map((i)=>(<li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cobalt-400 mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0" />{i}</li>))}</ul></div>))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-xl mb-10"><p class="sl">Values</p><h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-gray-900">How we build</h2></div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
        {[{n:"Open by Default",d:"Every platform, pipeline, and standard we develop is released openly."},{n:"Built for Scale",d:"We design for millions of genomes, not thousands."},{n:"Community Standards",d:"We work with consortia to ensure our infrastructure interoperates."},{n:"Reproducible by Design",d:"Containers, versioned workflows, and documentation are built in."}].map((v)=>(<div class="card"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">{v.n}</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">{v.d}</p></div>))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

<Fragment slot="footer"><Footer /></Fragment></Base>